        <section>

            <h3>Example: Showing Name Publicly</h3>

            <p>This says that the user's name will be shared publicly to all:</p>

            <pre class="prettyprint lang-json">
{
    "name": true
}
            </pre>

            <h3>Example: Showing Name in Context</h3>

            <p>Tightening the context some, a policy may say that the name will be shared to others in the context of the application (so that, for example, if it's a course forum tool, this would mean that names are shared with other members of the course:</p>

            <pre class="prettyprint lang-json">
{
    "name": {
        "context": true
    }
}
            </pre>

            <p>Implicitly, <var>public</var> is assumed <var>false</var> (as are all other unset info types except <var>system</var> and <var>research</var>).</p>

            <h3>Example: User Opting Out of Showing Name in Context</h3>

            <p>Giving the user a bit more freedom, one can also allow the user to opt out of sharing their name (such as listing them as "Anonymous User" in a forum tool), using the string <var>optOut</var>:</p>

            <pre class="prettyprint lang-json">
{
    "name": {
        "context": "optOut"
    }
}
            </pre>

            <h3>Example: User Opting In to Showing Name in Context</h3>

            <p>Conversely, <var>optIn</var> is also an allowed value, if the user's name were shown in context only if the user said it was okay first:</p>

            <pre class="prettyprint lang-json">
{
    "name": {
        "context": "optIn"
    }
}
            </pre>

            <h3>Example: Contacting Users for Marketing with Purchasing Support and No Location Tracking</h3>

            <p>This says that your application allows the user to opt out of being contacted by name and email for marketing purposes. Further, it says that a user can opt in for activity monitoring for the sake of profiling such as to deliver more targetted search results. It also explicitly states that the user's location is not tracked in any way, and that the system collects details used to allow the user to make purchases.</p>

            <pre class="prettyprint lang-json">
{
    "name": {
        "marketing": "optOut"
    },
    "contact": {
        "marketing": "optOut"
    },
    "activity": {
        "profiling": "optIn"
    },
    "location": false,
    "purchasing": {
        "system": true
    }
}
            </pre>

            <h3>Example: No Data Collected</h3>

            <pre class="prettyprint lang-json">
false
            </pre>

